body_html:
@617976080 - Hi, try one of the following.

  1. Run the following commands
    pip uninstall tensorflow
    pip install tensorflow --no-cache-dir
    See if you are running into the same error after trying the above commands.
    If the above solution doesn't work, please try the below one.

  2. Try upgrading numpy with the following command and see if you are running into this error.
    pip install numpy --upgrade --ignore-installed

@617976080  - Hi, try one of the following.

1) Run  the following commands
                **pip uninstall tensorflow
                pip install tensorflow --no-cache-dir**
See if you are running into the same error after trying the above commands.
If the above solution doesn't work, please try the below one.

2) Try upgrading numpy with the following command and see if you are running into this error.
**pip install numpy --upgrade --ignore-installed**
